NAME
	tk-gallery (tk-display) - render one of every core Tk widget class twice, engine defaults beside a flat and padded treatment, as a toolkit review instrument

INTERFACE
	tk-display (MatrixTkDisplay)

READS
	nothing (the mount argument is unused; pass /)

WRITES
	nothing

DESCRIPTION
	A review instrument for the toolkit's look, not a data view.  The
	left column renders label, button, checkbutton, radiobutton,
	entry, listbox, scale, scrollbar, and text exactly as the engine's
	defaults draw them (raised/sunken bevels, text-tight targets).
	The right column renders the same widgets in the proposed
	InferNode treatment: -relief flat -borderwidth 1 (2D, no bevels)
	and pack -ipadx/-ipady on interactive widgets — internal padding
	that grows the widget's actual hit target, per the 44pt/48dp
	minimum-touch-target conventions.

	Widgets carry representative content (entry text, list items, a
	set scale) so insets and bevels are visible in use.  Compare the
	columns, then decide the default treatment; per-widget options
	cover everything shown, and anything chosen as a DEFAULT belongs
	in the Tk engine (libtk) rather than in every module.

SEE ALSO
	video-ctl (a Tk control surface using padded targets)
	libtk/buton.c (relief and border defaults), libtk/xdata.c
	(generic -relief/-borderwidth options, supported relief values)
